{"cursor":"9710","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"'Patch Tuesday' is the second Tuesday of each month, on which Microsoft\nregularly releases security patches. Microsoft rarely refers to it as 'Patch\nTuesday'; here's one reference. {{cite web |url=http://blogs.msdn.com/b/outlook_mobile/archive/2008/11/12/wm-6-1-smtp-fix-\nreleased.aspx |title=Patch Tuesday: WM 6.1 SMTP fix released!\n|publisher=Microsoft - Outlook Mobile Team Blog |date=November 11, 2008\n|accessdate=November 9, 2011}} It is widely referred to it this way by\nthe industry. {{cite web |url=http://news.cnet.com/8301-10805_3-20118106-75/microsoft-patch-tuesday-to-\ntarget-windows-ie/ |title=Microsoft Patch Tuesday to target Windows, IE\n|publisher=CNet |date=October 10, 2011 |accessdate=November 9,\n2011}} Showing Microsoft referring to the 'second Tuesday of every\nmonth'  Starting with Windows 98, Microsoft included a \"Windows Update\"\nsystem that would check for patches to Windows and its components, which\nMicrosoft would release intermittently. With the release of Microsoft Update,\nthis system also checks for updates to other Microsoft products, such as Office,\nVisual Studio and SQL Server.\n\nPatch Tuesday begins at 18:00 or 17:00 GMT (10:00 PST (GMT-8) or 10:00 PDT (GMT-\n7)). Sometimes there is an extraordinary Patch Tuesday, 14 days after the\nregular Patch Tuesday. There are also updates which are published daily (e.g.\ndefinitions for Windows Defender and Microsoft Security Essentials) or\nirregularly.\n\nMicrosoft has an apparent pattern of releasing a larger number of updates in even-\nnumbered months, and fewer in odd-numbered months. [http://www.computerworl-\nd.com/s/article/9217501/Microsoft_slates_hefty_Patch_Tuesday_to_fix_34_flaws_ne-\nxt_week ComputerWorld: Microsoft slates hefty Patch Tuesday, to fix 34 flaws\nnext week] [http://www.itproportal.com/2011/06/10/microsoft-ready-patch-\n34-security-vulnerabilities/ ItProPortal: Microsoft Ready To Patch 34 Security\nVulnerabilities] [http://news.techworld.com/operating-\nsystems/3278043/microsoft-to-patch-critical-windows-server-vulnerability/\nTechWorld: Microsoft to patch critical Windows Server vulnerability]\n","linknr":171,"url":"patch_tuesday","recorded":1367713449,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Patch_Tuesday&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Patch_Tuesday&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","/wiki/Patch_Tuesday","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.wikihiero%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","/w/index.php?title=Patch_tuesday&redirect=no","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/Microsoft","#cite_note-1","#cite_note-2","#cite_note-3","/wiki/Windows_98","/wiki/Windows_Update","/wiki/Patch_(computing)","/wiki/Microsoft_Windows","/wiki/Microsoft_Update","/wiki/List_of_Microsoft_software_applications","/wiki/Microsoft_Office","/wiki/Microsoft_Visual_Studio","/wiki/Microsoft_SQL_Server","/wiki/Greenwich_Mean_Time","/wiki/Pacific_Standard_Time","/wiki/Pacific_Daylight_Time","#cite_note-4","#cite_note-5","#cite_note-6","#Patch-deployment_costs","#Security_implications","#.22Exploit_Wednesday.22","#Adoption_by_other_companies","#Bandwidth_impact","#See_also","#References","#External_links","/w/index.php?title=Patch_Tuesday&action=edit&section=1","/wiki/Windows_Update","#cite_note-7","/wiki/Exploit_(computer_security)","/w/index.php?title=Patch_Tues